      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "If SAVIENNE (8) is lining up again she is the one to beat. Was a top run fresh over a mile then tackled the Listed Belmont Oaks over the weekend finishing 11th behind Ladies Pro. Huge class drop for this and if on the quick turnaround and with Pike aboard gets a chance to atone. BIG MAN ZOR (4) is the clear danger. Not far away two back at Pinjarra then seventh and beaten only 2.5 lengths at Belmont latest. Looks ideally placed by the extra ground now. ROCKIN' ROBIN (3) raced on seed and boxed on for a distance fourth last time. Has the claim and will go forward. Can give a sight. CORSO VENEZIA (7) has had the blinkers added and can do much better.",
